.sp

.I val atan2 
: 
.B float -> float -> float
.sp

.B atan2 y x
returns the arc tangent of 
.B y /\&. x
\&.  The signs of 
.B x
and 
.B y
are used to determine the quadrant of the result\&.
Result is in radians and is between 
.B \-pi
and 
.B pi
\&.

.sp

.I val hypot 
: 
.B float -> float -> float
.sp

.B hypot x y
returns 
.B sqrt(x *\&. x + y *\&. y)
, that is, the length
of the hypotenuse of a right\-angled triangle with sides of length
.B x
and 
.B y
, or, equivalently, the distance of the point 
.B (x,y)
to origin\&.  If one of 
.B x
or 
.B y
is infinite, returns 
.B infinity
even if the other is 
.B nan
\&.

